### 1. The Mobile Web App (What the user sees)
This is a sleek, dark-themed website that loads instantly when the user scans the QR code. It is built using plain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It feels like a real app, but doesn't require downloading anything from the App Store.

### 2. The Java Backend (The Traffic Cop)
Written in Java, this is the core engine running on a computer at the parking lot. 
- ✅ It generates the secure API keys so hackers can't book free spots.
- ✅ It calculates the complex math for surge pricing.
- ✅ It acts as the bridge between the user's phone and the database.

### 3. The Database (The Memory Bank)
SnapPark uses a cloud database called **Neon (PostgreSQL)**. This is a giant spreadsheet in the sky that remembers everything securely.
- If the power goes out at the parking lot, no data is lost! ✅
- It keeps a permanent record of every vehicle, every payment, and every slot status.

